        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:29PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Anderson, or 11 miles north of Navasota, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
College Station, Bryan, Kurten, Wixon Valley, Anderson, Kyle Field,
Iola, Wellborn, Roans Prairie, Richards, and Carlos.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
